2008-10-21  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Merge the two manuals.
	* Makefile.am: Generate just vaucanson-manual.pdf.
	* taf-kit.tex: Remove developer mode tests; always include
	  the text.
	* vaucanson-developer-manual.tex: Remove.
	* vaucanson-manual.tex: Renamed to vaucanson-user-manual.tex,
	  and removed all the developer mode tests. Other than removing
	  "Developer's" from the title, the unified manual is the same
	  as the previous developer's manual, which makes it simpler to
	  find and ensures it is distributed. Yes, the manual needs a
	  rewrite, but at least this removes some unnecessary complexity.
	* vaucanson-user-manual.tex: Rename to above.

2008-10-21  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Small English fix.
	* developer.tex: Indefinites are often plural in (modern)
	  English.

