2008-10-09  Florian Lesaint  <florian.lesaint@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add BOOST_CPPFLAGS to python

	* vaucanswig/expand.sh: add BOOST_CPPFLAGS.

2008-10-09  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Add test for recent realtime bug.
	* tests/Makefile.am: Add realtime_test.xml.
	* tests/README: Mention realtime_test.xml.
	* tests/automata/char-b/realtime_test.xml: New.
	* tests/defs.in: Add realtime_test.
	* tests/vcsn-char-b.test: Add test for realtime.

2008-10-09  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Remove AC_CXX_FLAGS, CXXFLAGS_{OPTIMIZE,DEBUG} (closes #183).
	* build-aux/vcsn.m4: Remove AC_CXX_FLAGS and VCSN_WARN_CXXFLAGS.
	* configure.ac: Don't call AC_CXX_FLAGS.
	* doc/README.txt: Remove documentation for CXXFLAGS_{OPTIMIZE,DEBUG}.

2008-10-09  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Fix realtime good and proper.
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/realtime.hxx: realtime was
	  suffering from two bugs: first, it randomly failed, because
	  the iteration over the transitions was confused by the fact
	  that transitions were being deleted while it ran; secondly,
	  it did not deal properly with initial and final labels,
	  which for a realtime automaton should not have even one
	  letter. Finally, the structure of the code in do_realtime_words
	  tried to compensate for the fact that initial and final labels
	  are not transitions with some fairly hairy logic (and wrong, in
	  that it caused the second bug). This has been fixed: the cases
	  for initial and final states have been lifted out into
	  realtime_words_here, and do_realtime_words only deals with
	  transitions, in a cleaner way, and avoids the iterator problem
	  by copying the transitions into a vector and iterating over
	  that.

2008-10-09  Jerome Galtier  <jerome.galtier@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix contexts handling w.r.t. pipe_writers.hh.
	* taf-kit/src/Makefile.am: Define macro NO_SECOND_OPERATOR for
	  char-char and int-int instances to prevent `operator()'
	  redefinition in pipe_writers.
	* taf-kit/src/pipe_writers.hh,
	* taf-kit/src/pipe_writers.hxx: Add conditional function definition.

2008-10-09  Jerome Galtier  <jerome.galtier@lrde.epita.fr>

	Cleanup the identity algorithm.
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/internal/evaluation.hxx: Replace
	  incorrect header `projection.hh' by `image.hh' to be more
	  conservative on header inclusions.
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/projection.hh: Document the identity
	  function purpose by moving comments to right location. Add an
	  INTERFACE for the identity algorithm needed to prevent linkage
	  errors when building Vaucanson with "-O3". Remove out-of-context
	  header inclusions.
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/projection.hxx: Cosmetic changes.
	  Reorder headers.
	* include/vaucanson/contexts/fmp_transducer_functions.thh: Cosmetic
	  changes (Cleanup from patch [1575]). Add the domain and image
	  headers.
	* lib/generate_libvcsn.rb,
	* vaucanswig/expand.sh: Add condition filters for the
	  `projection.hh' file.

2008-10-09  Jerome Galtier  <jerome.galtier@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix wrong constructed type by standard_of_traits.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_base.hh
	(VCSN_MAKE_STANDARD_OF_TRAITS): Change the implementation of the
	automaton type constructed from a ratexp type, by changing the fifth
	template argument from `Tm' to `letter_t', where `letter_t' is now
	calculated from the monoid type (M), and by changing the last
	template argument from `NoTag' to `std::pair<double, double>'.
	This now construct an automaton type implementation corresponding
	to the one defined in generic_automaton_impl.thh, and thus makes true
	the predicate that "standard_of_traits must construct an automaton
	type that can receive an automaton constructed by standard_of".

2008-10-09  Jerome Galtier  <jerome.galtier@lrde.epita.fr>

	Improve libraries resilience to optimizations.
	* include/vaucanson/misc/contract.hh: Remove the `static' qualifier
	  from the function `trap'. It has the net effect of making
	  vcsn::misc::contract::trap a weak symbol, allowing user code to
	  overwrite it. This is what Taf-Kit does by setting the
	  EXCEPTION_TRAPS macro. Depending on compiler optimizations, having
	  the function as `static inline' could produce linkage errors.
	  Building Taf-Kit now, does not depend anymore on aggressive symbol
	  removals in libvcsn.

2008-10-09  Jerome Galtier  <jerome.galtier@lrde.epita.fr>

	Make vaucanswig ignore the rw_composition algorithm.
	* vaucanswig/expand.sh: Add new filter condition.

2008-10-09  Jerome Galtier  <jerome.galtier@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix compilation problems for non standard boost install paths.
	* src/tests/test-suites/test-suite.mk: Add missing BOOST_CPPFLAGS.

2008-10-09  Jerome Galtier  <jerome.galtier@lrde.epita.fr>

