2008-09-26  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	* taf-kit/demos/hulden/run.in: Run quotient after products, as
	suggested by Sylvain Lombardy.  Allow the test to be run in
	verbose mode if $VERBOSE is set.

2008-09-26  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix the new rules emitted in lib's makefile fragments to
	distribute source files and support VPATH builds.

	* lib/generate_libvcsn.rb (write_makefile): Compute
	type.gsub(/-/, "_") only once.  Output the list of source files in
	EXTRA_target_SOURCES, not in target_REALSOURCES, so that Automake
	distributes them and emit build rules for them (this way we can
	build a single object if we want).  Add all these files to
	MAINTAINERCLEANFILES.  Don't use tabulations while declaring
	variables, this is known to confuse automake.  Call write_all_cc.
	(write_all_cc): New function to generate all.cc files that
	include all the individual files.  The previous approach using
	cat did not cope with VPATH builds, and this way we do not have
	to fiddle with $(srcdir) and friends.

2008-09-26  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	* doc/Makefile.am (install-data-local): Fix the permissions
	of the installed documentation.  Reported by Reuben Thomas.

2008-09-26  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	Honor BOOST_CPPFLAGS and BOOST_LDFLAGS, set by AX_BOOST_BASE.

	* vaucanson.mk (AM_LDFLAGS): Define as $(BOOST_LDFLAGS).
	(AM_CPPFLAGS): USe $(BOOST_CPPFLAGS).
	* taf-kit/src/Makefile.am (AM_LDFLAGS): Append to the existing
	variable.

2008-09-25  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	* include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/letter.hh (LETTER_DEFAULT):
	Do not use const when an object is returned by copy; this
	removes a g++-4.3 warning.
	* include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/letter/char_letter.hxx
	(default_joker, default_other): Likewise.

2008-09-25  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/isomorph.hxx
	(test_correspondence): Add braces to kill a g++-4.3 warning.

