2008-09-25  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Add some ignore properties.

2008-09-25  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Write ChangeLog for r2182.
	* ChangeLog: Write what should have gone in r2182.

2008-09-25  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Build each library in lib/ as one source file.
	* generate_libvcsn.rb: Change Makefile rules to generate a
	  single intermediate all.cc file and compile that. Tests show
	  it builds about 70% faster than building the files separately.
	  As per vaucanson-private discussion today & yesterday, use
	  this method rather than just generating a single source file
	  in generate_libvcsn.rb directly, so that later we can have
	  a few (but not many) .cc files for tightly-coupled algorithms,
	  so that we don't have to rebuild entire libraries when only
	  changing one algorithm.

2008-09-25  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Add some ignore patterns to svn:ignore.

2008-09-25  Florian Lesaint  <florian.lesaint@lrde.epita.fr>

	- Update TAFKit parser grammar to support escaped characters.
	Any character can be escaped.
	Any special character that is escaped is seen as a basic letter.
	Everything is based on a simple "escape" function.
	It is currently not possible to have *(lex_escape_ch_p)[&fun]
	return an escaped sequence, it only works on a single char.
	- Solve ticket #171.
	- This fix does not enable the support of escaped characters in the
	rational expression parser.
	* taf-kit/src/parser_options.hxx: Add escape function.
	* taf-kit/src/parser_options.hh: Add escape function.
	* taf-kit/tests/vcsn-char-b.test: Add a test on the ascii alphabet.

2008-09-21  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Fix typo in header name.
	* src/tests/include/Makefile.am: transition_coherence_test.hh
	  was incorrectly spelt; fix spelling.

2008-09-20  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Fix boost tests not to export variables.
	Don't export CPPFLAGS or LDFLAGS, as this breaks configure -C.
	This bug was previously corrected in the old vcsn-boost.m4,
	which was just a copy of an older ax_boost_base.m4, in r1788.
	This time I've reported it upstream in an attempt to make sure this
	problem doesn't arise again.
	* build-aux/ax_boost_base.m4
	* build-aux/ax_boost_wserialization.m4

2008-09-19  Jimmy Ma  <jimmy.ma@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix buildsystem.
	* Makefile.am: Add missing file to noinst_HEADERS.

2008-09-19  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Update and improve BOOST tests.
	* build-aux/Makefile.am: Add new boost .m4 files.
	* build-aux/ax_boost_base.m4: New. This replaces vcsn-boost.m4 with
	  a more up-to-date version of the same file, with its upstream name.
	* build-aux/ax_boost_wserialization.m4: New. Used to detect the
	  BOOST serialization library.
	* build-aux/vcsn-boost.m4: Remove. See above.
	* configure.ac: Detect the serialization library explicitly. Add a
	  comment saying that we need to do the same thing for the graph
	  library, but there's currently no macro for that. I've asked
	  upstream for help.

2008-09-19  Reuben Thomas  <rrt@sc3d.org>

	Fix ChangeLog for my previous commits.
	* ChangeLog: Fix my previous entries.

2008-09-19  Florian Lesaint  <florian.lesaint@lrde.epita.fr>

	To enable the use of standalone rational expressions described in xml
	files, add the OUTPUT_TYPE_EXP and INPUT_TYPE_EXP possibilities.
	Split output_type in output_aut_type and output_exp_type to have
	different default output for automata (xml) and rational
	expressions (exp).
	* include/generate_headers.sh: split output_type.
	* taf-kit/src/common.hh: split output_type.
	* taf-kit/src/main.cc: split output_type.
	* taf-kit/src/pipe.hh: Add *_TYPE_EXP.
	* taf-kit/src/pipe.hxx: split output_type.
	* taf-kit/src/pipe_writers.hh: split output_type.
	* taf-kit/src/pipe_writers.hxx: split output_type. Prepare to support
	xml standalone rational expressions' files. Improve the error
	messages.

