	Remove useless 'using namespace'.
	Fix invalid reads which can occur after several graph copies.

  2008-01-10  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/determinize.hxx:
	Replace deltac by deltaf.

  2008-01-03  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hxx:
	remove useless debug.

  2008-01-03  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix a critical issue in BMI graph structure..
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/eps_removal.hxx: remove useless debug.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_support.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_support.hxx,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/graphcontainer.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hxx,
	* include/vaucanson/misc/hash.hh:
	The graph container stored hstate_t objects for the states in each
	transition.
	However, the equal operator defined on hstate_t compared the actual
	index of the state and not the pointer. When a state is deleted,
	another state is renumbered. Meanwhile, since the graph container is
	not notified of this change, its "ordered" property is completely
	broken. The solution is to store pointers to the actual index instead
	of hstate_t object.
	This patch fix many, many, many issues :D

  2008-01-02  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix shell scripts.
	* include/generate_headers.sh: Use a valid = operator.
	* src/tests/bin/generate-test-suite.sh: Add missing double quotes.

