  2007-11-24  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix missing headers in tarball.
	* include/generate_headers.sh: the .mk file was not correctly
	generated and the generated headers were not part of the tarball.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add new files in Makefile.am.
	* Makefile.am: here.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix compilation issues by using the new for_all* macros.
	* vaucanson/algorithms/domain.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/image.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/projection.hxx: the types were not correctly
	specified in the for_all* macros.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add new for_all_* macros.
	* vaucanson/misc/usual_macros.hh:
	Since we will be able to use various automata structures in a same
	function, we need to specify which types of which automaton we are
	currently using when iterating over a container for instance.
	AUTOMATON_TYPES* allowed that but not the for_all_* macros.
	It's fixed.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Remove a non-standard operator in Support.
	* vaucanson/misc/support.hh: Remove the operator.
	* vaucanson/xml/tools.hxx: Fix the code using it.
	Support containers had operator*() which returned the first
	element value of the container if there was only one element.
	Since it is not STL compliant I removed it.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Temporarily disable light implementation.
	* configure.ac: define legacy as default implementation.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/light_graph_impl.hh.bak: New.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/light_graph_impl.hh: Remove.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/light_graph_impl.hxx.bak: New.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/light_graph_impl.hxx: Remove.
	The context headers are not generated anymore for the light implementation.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Rename bootstrap.sh to  bootstrap.
	* bootstrap.sh: Remove.
	* bootstrap: New.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Adjust the bootstrap to find the correct version of Automake.
	* bootstrap.sh: here.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix various bugs in boostg implementation.
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hh,
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hxx: here.
	Update correctly the labels when calling "set_initial" and "set_final".
	has_state() doesn't check anymore whether the pointer contained in a
	hstate_t is in the graph. It just checks whether the integer could refer
	to a state.
	Some cleanup.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add support for deletion while iterating over a boostg container.
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_support.hxx,
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/vgraph_container.hxx:
	Since we usually iterate over all the states or transitions and
	some modifications are made in the graph, we want the containers
	to support such operations without invalidating the current iterator.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Change the default value of boostg's hstate_t.
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers.hxx:
	Since the hstate_t are used as integers but are actually a pointer
	and the comparison between two hstate_t is based on the pointed integer,
	we needed a default allocated integer.
	Fix segfaults....

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add a new functor to update initial and final state's label.
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_functors.hxx: here.

  2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Temporarily replace set<htransition_t> by list<htransition_t>.
	* vaucanson/algorithms/aut_to_exp.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/evaluation.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/internal/outsplitting.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/internal/skeleton.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/is_deterministic.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/letter_to_letter_composition.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/normalized.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/normalized_composition.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/product.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/standard.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/sum.hxx:
	Since I need a working version for today, I need to fix quickly
	some issues. currently I have an issue when I want to store boostg's
	htransition_t which store iterators. Sometimes two iterators are
	identical, thus transitions are missing in the set... I don't know
	why yet. My guess is that Boost uses the same iterator when there are
	duplicates.
	Anyway, I will change the delta* methods soon and this bug should be
	fixed at the same time.

  2007-11-22  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add new operators for boostg's hstate_t
	* vaucanson/automata/concept/handlers.hxx,
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers.hh,
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers_op.hxx:
	We want the hstate_t to behave like real integers even though they are
	actually pointers in the boostg implementation. Thus we needed proper
	operators for comparison.
	We also wanted to always display them as integer when passed to
	std::cout.

  2007-11-21  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix various bugs and update the method's prototype in boostg implementation.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hxx: here.
	The state deletion and the delta* were incorrect.
	Add more preconditions.
	Use iterator instead of pointers in htransition_t. It is faster and safer.
	It may be slower in delta* since htransition_t are copied in a container.
	However a solution is going to be applied soon :D

  2007-11-21  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix and cleanup tests.
	* src/tests/include/tests/automata/algos/graphs/sub_automaton_test.hh:
	Remove the use of the method "max()" which is deprecated since patch #1797.
	* src/tests/include/tests/automata/algos/label_aware_graphs/concat_test.hh:
	Remove some debug.

  2007-11-21  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	hstate_t and htransition_t are now passed as const references.
	* automata/concept/automata_base.hh,
	* automata/concept/automata_base.hxx,
	* automata/concept/automata_ops.hh,
	* automata/concept/automata_ops.hxx,
	* automata/concept/copy.hxx,
	* automata/implementation/automaton_view.hh,
	* automata/implementation/automaton_view.hxx,
	* automata/implementation/legacy_graph_impl.hh,
	* automata/implementation/legacy_graph_impl.hxx,
	* automata/implementation/light_graph_impl.hh,
	* automata/implementation/light_graph_impl.hxx,
	* automata/implementation/transpose_view.hh,
	* automata/implementation/transpose_view.hxx:
	Since handlers can now store various sort of data, we needed to avoid
	copies of such objects. Thus, I changed the prototypes of every op_*
	functions.

  2007-11-21  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Move implementation's specific code into its own directory.
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boost_functors.hxx: Remove,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_functors.hxx: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers.hh: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers.hxx: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers_op.hxx: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_support.hh: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_support.hxx: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/edge_value.hxx,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/initial_value.hxx,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/vgraph_container.hxx,
	* misc/support.hh,
	* misc/support.hxx:
	The boostg implementation need specializations of objects provided by
	Vaucanson. In order to clearly identify which specialization is related
	to which implementation, I decided to move the related code in a
	directory named like the implementation.
	This code need a serious cleanup. I'll do it next weeks. Be patient :p

  2007-11-15  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Remove hstate_t's dependency on integer.
	* include/Makefile.am: include new files in the tarball.

	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/handlers.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/handlers.hxx:
	This type declaration is a generic one which can be
	specialized as needed. A handler must be convertible to an unsigned
	and the constructor based on the contained type _must_ be explicitly
	called.

	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_base.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_base.hxx,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_ops.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_ops.hxx,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/automaton_view.hxx:
      	Introduce a new operator 'op_get_state'. The graph structure
	is now used as a builder for hstate_t objects.
	Since we want to refer to states both with integer and hstate_t we
	also provide two versions of each operator handling states.

	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy_graph_impl.hh: .
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy_graph_impl.hxx: .
	Add new preconditions and use unsigned instead of signed integer as IDs
	for the states.

	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy/legacy_handlers.hh: New.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy/legacy_handlers.hxx: New.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy/legacy_sparse_interval.hh: New.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy/legacy_sparse_interval.hxx: New.
	Split previous automata/concept/handlers.* and misc/sparce_interval.*
	files and move the code related to the legacy implementation in these
	new files.
	SparseInterval::max() has been removed and replaced by
	SparseInterval::back() for a better compatibility with STL containers.


	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/eps_removal.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/eval.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/minimization_hopcroft.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/minimization_moore.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/realtime.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/search.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/standard_of.hxx: .
	Various fixes to make these algorithms work with 'generic' hstate_t
	variables. Basically, we just needed to replace calls to
	SparseInterval::max().

	* include/vaucanson/misc/random.hh: .
	* include/vaucanson/misc/random.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/tools/automaton_tools.hh: .
	* include/vaucanson/tools/gen_random.hxx: .
	Make the random function dependent on the data type of the container.

	* taf-kit/src/edition_commands.hxx: make use of the get_state function.

  2007-11-15  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Update automaton XMLs in data.
