	use them to check quotient as well as a few other commands
	already tested.

2007-11-24  Guillaume Leroi  <guillaume.leroi@lrde.epita.fr>

	operator<< is used in namespace misc, but also in rat and
	algebra. There were overload resolution issues in rat and
	algebra. Probably the same problem than the is_finite bug.

	*include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/letter/couple_letter.hh:,
	* include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/letter/couple_letter.hxx:
	Move operator<< from namespace vcsn::misc to std. Move escaped
	characters container of op_parse to template parameters, there is no
	reason to restrain it to a std::list.

2007-11-20  The LRDE Buildbot  <tsuna@lrde.epita.fr>

	Adjust the bootstrap to find the correct version of Automake.
	* bootstrap.sh: Rename as...
	* bootstrap: ... this.  Use automake-1.10 when available.

2007-11-13  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	Kill more warnings from recent GCCs.

	* include/vaucanson/misc/global_timer.hh: Simplify.  The only
	caller in taf-kit/src/main.cc is already checking for the
	emptyness of the string, and the previous code was using !=
	to compare two char*.
	* taf-kit/src/common.hh (arguments_t::args, arguments_t::alphabet,
	arguments_t::alphabet2): Declare as const char*.
	* taf-kit/src/main.cc (alphabet::name, alphabet::alphabet): Idem.
	* taf-kit/src/pipe.hh, taf-kit/src/pipe.hxx (set_name): Take
	a const argument.

2007-11-13  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	According to Andrew Pinski in GCC bug 34073
        (http://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=34073)
	name lookup for overloaded template functions works
	as follows:
	1. The previous definitions are looked up at the point
	of the call at definition time (ignoring any overloaded
	definition they may be done later).
	2. An argument dependent lookup occurs at instantiation time
	but only in the namespace of the argument (this one takes
	into account overloaded definitions done after the call).

	Because we have plenty of such functions that are specialized
	after they are used, we need to rely on (2).  So this change
	moves all op_* functions into their argument's namespace (algebra).
	Fixing
	test-suites/boolean_transducer/coherence_state_transition-test
	with newer versions of GCC.  The test case of GCC bug 34073
	is a reduced version of coherence_state_transition-test done
	by Guillaume Leroi.

	* include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/alphabets_base.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/alphabets_base.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/freemonoid_base.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/freemonoid_base.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/monoid_base.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/monoid_base.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/semiring_base.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/semiring_base.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/series_base.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/concept/series_base.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/alphabets/alphabet_set.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/alphabets/alphabet_set.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/alphabets/decorated_alphabet.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/alphabets/decorated_alphabet.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/free_monoid/str_words.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/free_monoid/str_words.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/free_monoid/tools.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/free_monoid/tools.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/free_monoid_product/freemonoid_product_pair_str.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/free_monoid_product/freemonoid_product_pair_str.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/letter/int_letter.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/letter/int_letter.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/semiring/numerical_semiring.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/semiring/numerical_semiring.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/semiring/tropical_semiring.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/semiring/tropical_semiring.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/series/generalized.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/series/generalized.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/series/krat.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/series/krat.hxx,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/series/polynoms.hh,
	include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/series/polynoms.hxx
	(identity_value, op_add, op_assign, op_can_choose_non_starable,
	op_choose, op_choose_from_supp, op_choose_non_starable,
	op_contains, op_contains_e, op_convert, op_default, op_first,
	op_in_add, op_in_mirror, op_in_mul, op_in_star, op_in_transpose,
	op_is_finite, op_is_finite_app, op_length, op_letter_equality,
	op_max_size, op_mul, op_parse, op_rout, op_second,
	op_series_choose, op_series_get, op_series_set,
	op_series_structure, op_star, op_starable, op_support, op_xeq,
	zero_value): Move all this functions into the vcsn::algebra namespace.

2007-11-12  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	* include/vaucanson/xml/tools.hxx
	(vcsn::xml::tools::create_semiring): Use strcmp instead of != to
	compare two char*, killing another GCC 4.2.3 warning about
	"comparison with string literal results in unspecified behaviour".

2007-11-12  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	Kill "deprecated conversion from string constant to `char*'"
	warnings with GCC 4.2.3 (prerelease).

	* include/vaucanson/tools/dot_display.hh,
	include/vaucanson/tools/dot_display.hxx (vscn::tools::dot_display):
	Pass argv as "const char *const", not "char *const".
	* include/vaucanson/tools/xml_display.hh,
	include/vaucanson/tools/xml_display.hxx (vscn::tools::xml_display):
	Likewise.
	* include/vaucanson/tools/out_display.hh,
	include/vaucanson/tools/out_display.hxx (vscn::tools::out_display):
	Likewise.  Adjust call to execvp.

2007-11-09  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	* ChangeLog.1: Whitespace cleanup.

2007-11-09  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	* build-aux/vcsn-boost.m4 (AX_BOOST_BASE): Do not export
	CPPFLAGS and LDFLAGS.  This is pointless and breaks
	`configure -C'.

2007-11-08  Guillaume Leroi  <guillaume.leroi@lrde.epita.fr>

	Use alphabets of input transducer in 'to-rt'.
	* taf-kit/src/tdc_commands.cc: Use alphabets of input
	fmp-tranducer to construct output transducer in 'to-rt'
	algorithm.
	* taf-kit/tests/vcsn-tdc.test: Add a test to at least check
	that no exception is raised in a basic example.

2007-11-02  Alexandre Duret-Lutz  <adl@lrde.epita.fr>

	Make boolean_rw_transducers/invert-test PASS.

	* src/tests/include/tests/automata/algos/boolean_rw_transducers/invert_test.hh:
	Use string comparisons to compare rational expressions in this
	specific case.  The previous tree comparison failed to
	equate (a.(b.(a.b))) with (a.((b.a).b)).  String comparison is
	still gross and a real RatExp comparison would be welcome here.

