	Add missing include directives
	* algorithms/eps_removal_sp.hxx: Here.
	* xml/builders.hh: Here.

2007-07-23  Florian Lesaint  <florian.lesaint@lrde.epita.fr>

  Merge the following changes:
  - Timer,
  - fix bugs.

  2007-07-09  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Merge changes to timer into the trunk
	  * ChangeLog: .
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer.cc: .
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer.hh: .
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_gathering.cc: .
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_gathering.hh: .
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_gathering.hxx: .
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_graph.cc: .
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_graph.hh: .

	  Merge changes made in r1685 (branch timer) into the trunk.

  2007-07-09  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Change timer sytem call.
	  * timer.cc: Adjustements in timer printing.
	  * timer.hh: Adjustements to new type.
	  * timer_internal_gathering.cc,
	  * timer_internal_gathering.hh,
	  * timer_internal_gathering.hxx: New type for time representation.
	  * timer_internal_graph.cc,
	  * timer_internal_graph.hh: Adjustements to new type.

	  Change the system call that gets the system time
	  (getrusage (...) instead of times (...)).
	  Timer gains precision (+-4ms instead of +-10ms), and the
	  output is cleaner.
	  A new type for time representation is defined, along with
	  standard arithmetics, hence the heavy changes.
	  Inclusion chain (#include) changes slightly.

  2007-07-04  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Improve detection of the time unit in report
	  * timer.cc:
	  Improve detection of the time unit for large numbers of
	  tasks.

  2007-07-04  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Fix divide by zero
	  * timer_internal_graph.cc:
	  Change charge values from NaN to zero when total program time
	  is less than 1ms.

  2007-06-26  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Fix ugly code
	  * timer.cc,
	  * timer.hh,
	  * timer_internal_graph.cc,
	  * timer_internal_graph.hh:
	  Fix ugly code and a couple of typos.

  2007-06-25  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Add timer command-line options in taf-kit
	  * src/common.hh,
	  * src/main.cc:
	  Add two command-line options to taf-kit binaries.
	  The global timer in taf-kit can now be exported in
	  DOT format using --export-time-dot and in XML format
	  using --export-time-xml.

	  Additionally, --report-time now takes the verbose
	  level of the report as an optional parameter.

	  See ../include/vaucanson/misc/timer.hh for
	  documentation.

  2007-06-25  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Change time display in timer report
	  * global_timer.hh: Fix alignment.
	  * timer.cc,
	  * timer.hh,
	  * timer.hxx:
	  Change time display.
	  * timer_internal_gathering.cc,
	  * timer_internal_gathering.hh,
	  * timer_internal_gathering.hxx,
	  * timer_internal_graph.cc,
	  * timer_internal_graph.hh,
	  * timer_internal_graph.hxx,
	  Fix naming conventions, untabify.

	  The unit used to display times in the standard report
	  is now adjusted automatically.

	  Add some documentation in timer.hh

  2007-06-21  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Add timer XML export, fix several issues.
	  * bencher.cc: Fix a typo.
	  * global_timer.hh: Add dump macro.
	  * timer.cc:
	  Add dump method to Timer.
	  Change behavior of arithmetic operators slightly.
	  Fix task ordering in display.
	  * timer.hh:
	  Add dump method to Timer.
	  Add documentation on command-line options in vaucanson.
	  * timer_internal_graph.cc,
	  * timer_internal_graph.hh,
	  * timer_internal_graph.hxx: Add internal dump method.

	  Timer instances can now be exported in XML format
	  using Timer.dump (Stream).
	  The structure of the XML output is far from definitive.

	  Information on command-line options for taf-kit regarding
	  the global timer is added to include/misc/timer.hh.

	  Summing timers now also sums calls, making the bencher
	  output logical.

	  Long task names are now truncated in standard display.

  2007-06-20  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Split timer.* into smaller files & add documentation
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/global_timer.hh:
	  Make it work outside vaucanson.
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer.cc:
	  Remove implementation of misc::Timer internal classes.
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer.hh:
	  Remove declaration of misc::Timer internal classes.
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer.hxx:
	  Move inline methods of misc::Timer here
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_gathering.cc,
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_gathering.hh,
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_gathering.hxx:
	  Move declaration & implementation of misc::Timer internal
	  classes regarding data gathering in those three files.
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_graph.cc,
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_graph.hh,
	  * include/vaucanson/misc/timer_internal_graph.hxx:
	  Move declaration & implementation of misc::Timer internal
	  classes regarding result computation in those three files.
	  * taf-kit/src/common.hh,
	  * taf-kit/src/main.cc:
	  Change global timer name from timer to global_timer to avoid
	  conflicts with the new namespace.

	  Former private classes of misc::Timer are now in the separate
	  namespace misc::timer.  Minor changes are made to the taf-kit
	  source to work with the new implementation.
	  Documentation is provided in include/vaucanson/misc/timer.hh.

	  Clean source code (thanks for pointing out what was wrong).


  2007-06-18  Florent DHalluin  <d-halluin@lrde.epita.fr>

	  Update timer and bencher for taf-kit
	  * bencher.cc,
	  * global_timer.hh,
	  * timer.cc,
	  * timer.hh,
	  * timer.hxx:

	  The implementation of the timer used in taf-kit changes:
	  it now builds a graph of the results using Graph from Boost.
	  Bencher is modified to work with the new implementation.
	  All current macro names used in taf-kit still work, and new
	  ones are added to access new features, such as export of
	  the graph in DOT language.
	  Basic documentation will be provided within a few days.
	  NOTE: taf-kit might not compile in this revision.

