2007-02-22  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix invalid iterator after deletion of an item
	Calling the set_final method in a loop iterating on the final states
	set can lead to invalid iterators, since set_final can delete an
	item in this set under certain circumstancies.
	This patch fix this problem.
	* include/vaucanson/algebra/implementation/letter/couple_letter.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/extension.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/fmp_to_realtime.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/invert.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/realtime_to_fmp.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/standard_of.hxx: .

2007-02-22  Guillaume Leroi  <guillaume.leroi@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add a implementation of eps-removal for automaton with multiplicity in B.
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/eps_removal.hxx: Do it. Adapt facade to
	call the boolean version.
	* taf-kit/tests/automata/tdc/t2_u-compose_u2.xml: Adapt it.
	t2_u-compose_u2.xml is still the same, but the new implementation of
	eps-removal does not give the same state order as before.

2007-02-22  Jimmy Ma  <jimmy.ma@lrde.epita.fr>

